ownedComment.body: Reports when the settings applied when executing the Start command match the current settings. This event is triggered when a setting is updated while in the summary state EnabledState and when the Start command is executed. The content of the event is determined by matching the currently applied settings to the settings applied by the start command. When the Start command is executed this event will always trigger with a True value because no settings have changed since the last start command.

Reports an error code when the summary state transitions to the FaultState. Error codes reserved for this component are XXX to XXX. When the Start command is executed the error code is reset to 0 and published. For more information on warnings and faults please see LTS-441.
Publish recommended settings in the form of settings version and labels using a comma separated value string.
Reports the summary state on each state transition.
An enumeration indicating the subsystem summary state. See the SummaryStateValue enumeration defined in the Typedefs package.
